12 (a) It is the policy of the State:
13 (1) to provide for fair housing throughout the State to all, regardless of
14 race, color, religion, sex, familial status, national origin, marital status, sexual orientation,
15 gender identity, disability, source of income, or military status; and
16 (2) to that end, to prohibit discriminatory practices OR ACTS THAT HAVE
17 A DISCRIMINATORY EFFECT, REGARDLESS OF INTENT, with respect to residential
18 housing by any person, in order to protect and ensure the peace, health, safety, prosperity,
19 and general welfare of all.
20 (b) This subtitle:
21 (1) is an exercise of the police power of the State for the protection of the
22 people of the State; and
23 (2) shall be administered and enforced by the Commission and, as provided
24 in this title, enforced by the appropriate State court.
25 20–705.
26 (A) Except as provided in SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION AND §§ 20–703
27 and 20–704 of this subtitle, a person may not, REGARDLESS OF INTENT:
28 (1) refuse to sell or rent after the making of a bona fide offer, refuse to
29 negotiate for the sale or rental of, or otherwise make unavailable or deny, a dwelling to any
30 person because of race, color, religion, sex, disability, marital status, familial status, sexual
31 orientation, gender identity, national origin, source of income, or military status;

